Data Type	               Type	                      Storage Size	             Precision	                            Syntax	                                    Use Case
DECIMAL(m,d)	       Fixed-point	                    Varies by m	                Exact (up to 65 digits)	            DECIMAL(10,2)	                            Currency, accounting
NUMERIC(m,d)	       Fixed-point	                    Same as DECIMAL	            Exact (alias of DECIMAL)	        NUMERIC(8,3)	                            Same as DECIMAL
FLOAT(p)	           Floating-point	                4 bytes	                    Approx. 7 decimal digits	        FLOAT or FLOAT(24)	                        Scientific, speed-priority tasks
DOUBLE	               Floating-point	                8 bytes	                    Approx. 15â€“17 digits	            DOUBLE or FLOAT(53)	                        High precision float calc.
REAL	               Floating-point	                Depends on config	        Either alias for DOUBLE or FLOAT	Depends on config	                        Varies by SQL mode






where m is the total number of digits